<div style=3D"float: right;padding-top:2pt"></div><h1 id=3D"hid1" class=3D"=
section">Gram-Schmidt process</h1>
<p class=3D"author">by <span itemprop=3D"author" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D=
"https://schema.org/Person"><a class=3D"author" id=3D"article-author" href=
=3D"https://www.statlect.com/about/#author">Marco Taboga</a></span>, PhD</p=
>
<p>
   The Gram-Schmidt process (or procedure) is a sequence of operations that=
 allow
   us to transform a set of linearly independent vectors into a set of
   orthonormal vectors that span the same space spanned by the original set=
.
</p>
<div class=3D"artContainer">
   <span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"statlectArt" width=3D"750" heigh=
t=3D"2865" src=3D"https://www.statlect.com/images/gram-schmidt-orthogonaliz=
ation.png" alt=3D"Infographic summarizing the main steps of the Gram-Schmid=
t orthogonalization algorithm."></span>
</div>



<p><img width=3D"29" height=3D"24" src=3D"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgo=
AAAANSUhEUgAAAB0AAAAYCAIAAACJPGHrAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAA=
