<h2 id=3D"hid7" class=3D"subsection">Every inner product space has an ortho=
normal basis</h2>
<p>
   The following proposition presents an important consequence of the
   Gram-Schmidt process.
</p>
<div class=3D"proposition">
   <p><span class=3D"titoletto">Proposition</span>
      Let
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -4161px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>
      be a vector space equipped with an inner product
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"32" height=3D"26" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq5]" style=3D"background-position:0px -3526px;ver=
tical-align:-5px"></span>.
      If
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -4161px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>
      has finite
       <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/dimension-of-a-li=
near-space">dimension</a>
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"78" height=3D"26" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq67]" style=3D"background-position:0px -2645px;ve=
rtical-align:-5px"></span>,
      then there exists an orthonormal basis
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"65" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq68]" style=3D"background-position:0px -3026px;ve=
rtical-align:-5px"></span>
      for
      <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=
=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAA=
AICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -4161px;verti=
cal-align:-5px"></span>.
   </p>
</div>

<div class=3D"bproof"><span class=3D"bproof">Proof</span></div>
<div id=3D"idn3" class=3D"clps"><div class=3D"proofline">
<p>Since
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -4161px;vertical-=
align:-5px"></span>
   is finite-dimensional, there exists at least one basis for
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -4161px;vertical-=
align:-5px"></span>,
   consisting of
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"14" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"K" style=3D"background-position:0px -4137px;vertical-al=
ign:-5px"></span>
   vectors
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"94" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq69]" style=3D"background-position:0px -2433px;vertic=
al-align:-5px"></span>.
   We can apply the Gram-Schmidt procedure to the basis and obtain an ortho=
normal
   set
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"65" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq68]" style=3D"background-position:0px -3026px;vertic=
al-align:-5px"></span>.
   Since
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"65" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq71]" style=3D"background-position:0px -3002px;vertic=
al-align:-5px"></span>
   is a basis, it  <a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/matrix-algebra/linea=
r-span">spans</a>
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -4161px;vertical-=
align:-5px"></span>.
   Therefore,
   <span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp2" width=3D"275" height=3D"38"=
 src=3D"https://www.statlect.com/images/Gram-Schmidt-process__132.png" alt=
=3D"[eq72]"></span>Thus,
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"65" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq29]" style=3D"background-position:0px -2954px;vertic=
al-align:-5px"></span>
   is an orthonormal basis of
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"11" height=3D"25" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"$S$" style=3D"background-position:0px -4161px;vertical-=
